To automate selecting all checkboxes on a page and then clicking a "Save" button in JavaScript, you can use the following approach:

1. Select all checkboxes.
2. Check each checkbox.
3. Click the "Save" button.

Here's a simple example:

```javascript
// Select all checkboxes
const checkboxes = document.querySelectorAll('input[type="checkbox"]');

// Check each checkbox
checkboxes.forEach(checkbox => {
    checkbox.checked = true;
});

// Assuming the save button has an id of 'saveButton'
document.getElementById('saveButton').click();
```

If the "Save" button does not have an ID, you can select it by its class or other attributes:

```javascript
document.querySelector('.save-button-class').click();
```

Make sure to adjust the selector according to your actual HTML structure.

